{{ pc.standardSection('id="protocol-trace-observability"') }}
    <h3 id="ssr-contract">Trace Observability Protocol</h3>
    <p>
        Aligns Web Traces with <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/trace-context/">W3C Trace Context</a>
        and <a href="https://opentelemetry.io/">OpenTelemetry</a>. Defines the trace propagation
        contract servers and clients must observe so distributed traces correlate across the
        client/server boundary, plus the suggested client-side API shape (<code>trace()</code> /
        <code>effect()</code>) that components instrument against.
    </p>

    <h4>Suggested Client API Shape</h4>
    <we-code-view><pre><code>trace(value, { attributes });
effect(operation, { input, output, attributes });
    </code></pre></we-code-view>
    <p>Compatible with both distributed and local tracing needs; aligns with OpenTelemetry's span/context model.</p>

    <h4>Trace Context Propagation</h4>
    <p>
        <strong>Web Traces</strong> is primarily a client-side observability system. The server plays a role in
        propagating trace context so client-side spans correlate with server-side traces.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-gray-600 text-sm">
        <li><strong>Header propagation:</strong> Server MUST propagate <code>traceparent</code> and <code>tracestate</code> headers per the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/trace-context/">W3C Trace Context</a> specification.</li>
        <li><strong>Trace ID embedding:</strong> Server MAY embed the trace ID in a <code>&lt;meta&gt;</code> tag so client-side traces can reference the server trace:
<we-code-view><pre style="margin: 0.5rem 0; font-size: 0.8em;"><code>&lt;meta name="trace-id" content="00-4bf92f3577b34da6a3ce929d0e0e4736-00f067aa0ba902b7-01"&gt;</code></pre></we-code-view>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Client-only:</strong> All span creation, context propagation, sampling, attribute attachment, and exporter configuration are client-side operations. No server rendering contract is needed for trace instrumentation.</li>
    </ul>
{{ pc.endStandardSection() }}

{{ pc.standardSection('id="protocol-session-replay-envelope"') }}
    <h3 id="session-replay-envelope">Session-Replay Envelope Protocol</h3>
    <p>
        Ratified in <a href="/backlog/992-design-the-trace-replay-substrate-webtraces-webevents-the-14/">#992</a>.
        A <strong>thin binding/ordering</strong> contract for lightweight local session replay — an ordered
        session of Web Traces spans plus <strong>correlated references</strong> to three artifacts whose schemas
        it redefines none of:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-gray-600 text-sm">
        <li><strong>Snapshot</strong> — the <a href="/projects/webcontexts/">Web Contexts</a> serialization (<code>&lt;script type="context"&gt;</code>) is the replay starting state.</li>
        <li><strong>Journal (the determinism anchor)</strong> — the <a href="/projects/webstates/">Web States</a> <code>ChangeRecord</code> journal is <em>re-applied</em> to the snapshot, executing <strong>no application JavaScript</strong> (anchor A — deterministic over journaled state).</li>
        <li><strong>Action identity (correlation)</strong> — <a href="/projects/webevents/">Web Events</a> typed-event identity labels which action caused which diffs; correlation/comprehension only, <strong>not</strong> load-bearing for journaled-state determinism.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Required invariants (#992 amendment)</h4>
    <ol class="list-decimal ml-6 text-gray-600 text-sm">
        <li><strong>Snapshot↔journal consistency precondition.</strong> The snapshot reference carries a
            version/hash (reusing <code>ChangeRecord.version</code>) that the journal asserts it applies onto;
            a replayer <strong>refuses or flags</strong> a drifted snapshot rather than applying diffs blindly.</li>
        <li><strong>Off-journal-state boundary.</strong> Non-journaled state (imperative DOM focus/scroll,
            refs, non-store locals) is <strong>out of replay scope</strong> by contract. The optional
            <strong>behavioral-replay</strong> mode (re-fold actions through handlers — where Web Events
            identity <em>is</em> load-bearing) is the documented escape hatch for faithful off-journal repro.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>
        The contract type + structural validator ship at <code>we:plugs/webtraces/sessionReplayEnvelope.ts</code>;
        behavioral conformance vectors at <code>we:conformance-vectors/session-replay-envelope.vectors.ts</code>
        judge a replayer's observable outcome (drift-refused vs. applied; off-journal disclosed vs. reproduced).
    </p>
{{ pc.endStandardSection() }}
